'''Karsten E. Whitson''' (born August 25, 1991) is an American [[college baseball]] player. A [[pitcher]], Whitson attends the [[University of Florida]] and plays for the [[Florida Gators baseball]] team.

A first round pick in the [[2010 Major League Baseball Draft|2010 Major League Baseball (MLB) Draft]] out of high school, Whitson opted to attend college, and was considered a top prospect in the [[2013 MLB Draft]] until his shoulder surgery. Whitson was drafted by the [[Washington Nationals]] in the 37th round of the 2013 Draft.

==Career==
Whitson attended [[Chipley High School]] in [[Chipley, Florida]]. As a senior, Whitson pitched to a 0.62 [[earned run average]] (ERA) and recorded 123 [[strikeout]]s in 55 [[innings pitched]]. ''[[Baseball America]]'' ranked Whitson the third best high school prospect in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/sports/college/college-baseball-freshman-karsten-whitson-pitches-/nLqGk/ |title=College baseball: Freshman Karsten Whitson pitches Florida to swe |publisher=www.palmbeachpost.com |date=2011-02-20 |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref> He played in the Aflac [[All-America]] game and pitched in the Pan American Junior Baseball Championship.<ref>{{cite web|author=10:32 p.m. |url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2010/jun/07/san-diego-picks-rare-pitcher/ |title=San Diego picks a <U+2018>rare<U+2019> pitcher |publisher=UTSanDiego.com |date=2010-06-07 |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref>

The [[San Diego Padres]] selected Whitson in the first round, with the ninth overall selection, of the [[2010 Major League Baseball Draft]]. Despite the Padres offering Whitson a [[signing bonus]] of $2.1 million, he opted not to sign, surprising the Padres front office.<ref name=yahoo/><ref>{{cite web|author=By BERNIE WILSON, AP Sports Writer 11:14 p.m.Aug. 16, 2010 |url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2010/aug/16/padres-rhp-whitson-fail-to-agree-to-terms/ |title=Padres, RHP Whitson fail to agree to terms |publisher=UTSanDiego.com |date=2010-08-16 |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref> Whitson reportedly asked for $2.7 million,<ref>{{cite web|last=Kenney |first=Kirk |url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2011/jun/27/ex-padres-draft-pick-flourishing-florida/ |title=Ex-Padres draft pick flourishing with Florida |publisher=UTSanDiego.com |date=2011-06-27 |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref> but stated that he felt he was not ready for the challenge of [[minor league baseball]].<ref name=yahoo>{{cite web|last=Rogers |first=Kendall |url=http://rivals.yahoo.com/ncaa/baseball/news?slug=kr-whitson111010 |title=Florida<U+2019>s Whitson explains why he spurned $2.1M - College Baseball - Rivals.com |publisher=Rivals.yahoo.com |date=2010-11-10 |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref>

Whitson enrolled at the [[University of Florida]], and joined the [[Florida Gators baseball]] team, pitching in the [[Southeastern Conference]]. As a freshman, Whitson pitched to a 8<U+2013>1 [[win-loss record (pitching)|win-loss record]], with a 2.40 ERA and 92 strikeouts in 97 innings.<ref>{{cite web|author=By Kirk Kenney, Special to SI.com |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2012/baseball/more/02/13/college.baseball.preview.top.8/index.html |title=Florida, Stanford looking to deny South Carolina another CWS title <U+2013> SI.com <U+2013> MLB |publisher=Sportsillustrated.cnn.com |date= |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref> He was named a Freshman [[All-America]]n by ''[[Collegiate Baseball Newspaper]]''.<ref>{{cite web|date=June 8, 2011|first=Rachel|last=George|publisher=Orlando Sentinel |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2011-06-08/sports/os-karsten-whitson-all-american-20110608_1_gators-mlb-draft-sec |title=Karsten Whitson: Gators pitcher Karsten Whitson named Freshman All-American |accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref>

Whitson pitched to a 4<U+2013>0 with a 3.51 ERA in 2012 as a sophomore. He will miss the entire 2013 season due to a shoulder injury that required surgery, which was performed by Dr. [[James Andrews (physician)|James Andrews]]. His [[Glenoid labrum|labrum]] and [[rotator cuff]] were undamaged.<ref>{{cite web|date=February 13, 2013|first=Edgar|last=Thompson |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2013-02-13/sports/os-florida-gators-news-0214-20130213_1_karsten-whitson-kevin-o-sullivan-shoulder |title=Gators starting pitcher Karsten Whitson out with a shoulder injury|publisher=Orlando Sentinel|accessdate=2013-02-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/sports/college-baseball/florida-pitcher-karsten-whitson-will-miss-season-w/nWQPG/|title=Florida Gators pitcher Karsten Whitson will miss season with shoulder injury|first=Greg|last=Luca|newspaper=The Palm Beach Post|date=February 15, 2013|accessdate=February 24, 2013}}</ref> The [[Washington Nationals]] selected Whitson in the 37th round, with the 1,126th overall selection, in the [[2013 MLB Draft]].<ref>http://blogs.palmbeachpost.com/gatorbytes/2013/06/08/former-no-9-overall-pick-karsten-whitson-is-selected-1126th-in-mlb-draft/</ref>

==Personal==
Whitson's parents both graduated from the University of Florida.<ref name=yahoo/>

